Given a string and an integer k, find/count all substrings of length k where every character is unique.

Example

String = "abcabc"
k = 3

Possible substrings of length 3:

"abc" ✅ (all unique)
"bca" ✅
"cab" ✅
"abc" ✅

Answer = 4


Solution:
val s = "abccde"    
val k= 3

fun distinctSubString(s:String,k:Int):Int {
    var count = 0
	  val map = mutableMapOf<Char,Int>()
    
    for(i in 0 until k){
        map[s[i]] = map.getOrDefault(s[i],0)+1
    }
    if(map.size == k){ count++ }
    
    for(i in k until s.length){

       map[s[i]] = map.getOrDefault(s[i],0) + 1
        
        val prev = s[i - k]
        map[prev] = map.getOrDefault(prev,0) - 1
        
        if(map[prev] == 0){ map.remove(prev) }

        if(map.size == k){ count++ }
    }
  
    return count
}
